quest_title: There are 300 students in a college. If every student reads 5 newspapers and each newspaper is read 60 times, how many newspapers are there?
explanation_txt:
Let the required number be \(x\)

Calculating no. of times newspapers are read(N), \(N = \textrm {no. of students} \times \textrm{no. of newspaper a student reads} \)

This gives, \(N=1500\).

But, \(N = \textrm {no. of times a newspaper is read} \times \textrm{no. of newspapers} \).

Then, \(N = 60x\).

Finally, \(60x = 1500\) gives \(x= 25\)
